FBIS4-14032 "drnes080_o_94002" FBIS-NES-94-080 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 SYRIA Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Visits Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Visits Makes Statement JN2504141294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1115 GMT 25 Apr 94 JN2504141294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets and the delegation accompanying him arrived in Damascus at noon today on a three-day official visit to Syria. He was received at Damascus International Airport by Dr. Salim Yasin, deputy prime minister for economic affairs; Dr. Muhammad al-'Imadi, minister of economy and foreign trade; several Foreign Ministry officials; Aleksandr Zotov, the Russian ambassador in Damascus; and the Embassy staff. In a statement to the SYRIAN ARAB NEWS AGENCY, SANA, correspondent, Soskovets expressed his happiness over his visit to Syria, and said: My visit to Syria is linked to President Yeltsin's decision to continue and promote economic and political relations with Syria. He added: Our country has long-standing relations with Syria, and now that it has become an independent and sovereign state, we want to promote and expand previous relations and cooperation between the two countries.
